1
00:00:07,458 --> 00:00:12,416
♪


2
00:01:40,916 --> 00:01:43,625
[MAN A]
Yes. Yes, that's right.

3
00:01:43,708 --> 00:01:46,166
I think it'll be done shortly.

4
00:01:46,250 --> 00:01:47,625
Exactly.

5
00:01:47,708 --> 00:01:51,041
Listen. You think you could
wait a little bit longer?

6
00:02:02,375 --> 00:02:05,041
[AKANE hums]

7
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:07,875
[YUTA groans]

8
00:02:07,958 --> 00:02:12,916
[AKANE humming]

9
00:02:18,833 --> 00:02:23,791
[AKANE continues humming]

10
00:02:28,291 --> 00:02:30,583
Oh. You're awake.

11
00:02:30,666 --> 00:02:32,875
Good morning. If it is.

12
00:02:32,958 --> 00:02:34,375
I started to worry about you

13
00:02:34,458 --> 00:02:36,958
when I couldn't get
you to wake up.

14
00:02:37,041 --> 00:02:38,583
[YUTA]
Um...

15
00:02:38,666 --> 00:02:40,791
[AKANE]
Hm?

16
00:02:40,875 --> 00:02:42,583
[YUTA]
Who are you?

17
00:02:44,958 --> 00:02:46,458
Are you alright?

18
00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:52,125
Did you hit your head?
Do you know who you are?

19
00:02:52,208 --> 00:02:55,500
[AKANE gasps]
You've got amnesia!

20
00:02:57,625 --> 00:02:59,208
[YUTA grunts]

21
00:03:04,041 --> 00:03:05,291
[YUTA gasps]

22
00:03:09,541 --> 00:03:11,958
[YUTA]
Hm... Huh?

23
00:03:12,041 --> 00:03:14,750
You there. What're you doing?

24
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:18,083
Huh? Uh. I'm sorry, I'll go!

25
00:03:18,166 --> 00:03:21,208
Ugh! So this is where
you ran off to!

26
00:03:21,291 --> 00:03:23,208
Yuta, you shouldn't be
wandering around alone

27
00:03:23,291 --> 00:03:24,833
while you have amnesia!

28
00:03:24,916 --> 00:03:27,583
Yuta... Wait, is that my name?

29
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:29,500
Yup. Yuta Hibiki.

30
00:03:29,583 --> 00:03:32,250
Mama. I'm going to take
him to the hospital.

31
00:03:37,125 --> 00:03:39,250
[YUTA]
The mist sure is thick.

32
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:40,541
[AKANE]
Is it?

33
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:02,458
[YUTA]
Huh?

34
00:04:07,416 --> 00:04:08,625
[YUTA]
What is this?

35
00:04:08,708 --> 00:04:11,958
Something you always wear.
It's my wristwatch.

36
00:04:13,625 --> 00:04:15,666
[AKANE]
So, how'd it go?

37
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:18,166
A lot of it went
over my head but,

38
00:04:18,250 --> 00:04:20,416
they said I'd be back
to normal before long.

39
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:22,750
Oh yeah? That's awesome news!

40
00:04:22,833 --> 00:04:24,250
[YUTA chuckles]

41
00:04:24,333 --> 00:04:27,666
Well, guess I better head
on home. Thanks for everything.

42
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:29,958
Sure. But do you
know where you live?

43
00:04:30,041 --> 00:04:31,958
[YUTA]
Uh...!

44
00:04:32,041 --> 00:04:33,458
[AKANE]
I'll take you there.

45
00:04:39,291 --> 00:04:43,416
[YUTA] So, hey. Why was I
sleeping over at your house?

46
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:45,375
You were coming
home from school.

47
00:04:45,458 --> 00:04:47,541
Then you collapsed
and slept at my place.

48
00:04:47,625 --> 00:04:50,583
What do you mean?
Uh, do we have a history?

49
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:52,708
Like, uh... are we friends?

50
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:56,833
Well, actually, you and I
are boyfriend and girlfriend.

51
00:04:56,916 --> 00:04:59,916
Huh?! Oh, well that's
good to know.

52
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,916
You don't remember, do you?

53
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,125
Nope. Nothing.

54
00:05:04,208 --> 00:05:06,916
But, well, I can't help but
feel I lucked out a bit.

55
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:10,125
That's cruel! How could
you say that?

56
00:05:10,208 --> 00:05:11,791
This guy, unbelievable.

57
00:05:11,875 --> 00:05:14,208
[YUTA gasps]
Wait!

58
00:05:17,791 --> 00:05:21,291
[YUTA] Huh? Hey!
I didn't mean it! Really!

59
00:05:22,375 --> 00:05:24,083
[AKANE]
Well, this is where you live.

60
00:05:24,166 --> 00:05:25,916
[YUTA]
Right. Thank you.

61
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,833
[AKANE]
I'll be going home then.

62
00:05:27,916 --> 00:05:30,791
[YUTA]
Oh, okay. See you later.

63
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:35,541
--[AKANE] Boo.
--[YUTA gasps]

64
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:38,208
[AKANE giggles]
What, no kiss or anything?

65
00:05:38,291 --> 00:05:39,833
[YUTA gasps]

66
00:05:42,125 --> 00:05:45,875
[AKANE] Got you!
I'll see you tomorrow!

67
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,958
I think my heart stopped.

68
00:05:49,041 --> 00:05:51,125
[YUTA]
I'm home.

69
00:05:51,208 --> 00:05:52,791
It's dark.

70
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,458
[YUTA]
Hm?

71
00:06:07,583 --> 00:06:12,166
[YUTA] Losing my memory
might not be so bad.

72
00:06:19,833 --> 00:06:23,500
[RIKKA] Excuse me? I'm not
feeling very well today.

73
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:34,083
[AKANE]
Nobody's here.

74
00:06:34,166 --> 00:06:35,708
You skipping class too?

75
00:06:35,791 --> 00:06:37,333
Your name's Shinjo, right?

76
00:06:37,416 --> 00:06:39,000
[AKANE]
Just call me Akane.

77
00:06:39,083 --> 00:06:42,750
Those club introductions were
taking forever to get through.

78
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:44,416
You thinking of joining one?

79
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:47,000
Yeah, I'm leaning towards no.

80
00:06:47,083 --> 00:06:49,000
Back in middle school we
were forced to sign up,

81
00:06:49,083 --> 00:06:51,916
but now that I have a choice,
I'd rather just go home.

82
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,916
I totally agree,
no club for me either.

83
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,875
So where did you go
to middle school?

84
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:59,750
I'm from Matsugasaki.

85
00:06:59,833 --> 00:07:01,416
My secret.

86
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:02,875
[RIKKA]
What the heck?

87
00:07:02,958 --> 00:07:05,458
And here I was thinking you
took everything seriously.

88
00:07:05,541 --> 00:07:07,916
[AKANE giggling]
Me? Please.

89
00:07:09,416 --> 00:07:10,750
[AKANE]
But if you're curious for real,

90
00:07:10,833 --> 00:07:13,208
I actually moved to the
area just this spring.

91
00:07:13,291 --> 00:07:14,583
[RIKKA gasps]
You did?

92
00:07:14,666 --> 00:07:15,708
[AKANE]
As a matter of fact,

93
00:07:15,791 --> 00:07:17,958
my house is right
next door to yours.

94
00:07:18,041 --> 00:07:19,125
Haven't you noticed?

95
00:07:19,208 --> 00:07:20,375
[RIKKA]
You're kidding me!

96
00:07:20,458 --> 00:07:25,000
Wow, incredible! I mean,
what a huge coincidence!

97
00:07:25,083 --> 00:07:27,583
Yup, a huge coincidence.

98
00:07:32,208 --> 00:07:33,250
[AKANE]
Utsumi, right?

99
00:07:33,333 --> 00:07:36,208
[UTSUMI]
Huh? Sh-Shinjo?

100
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:39,375
How come you're
dressed up all fancy?

101
00:07:39,458 --> 00:07:42,125
Oh. I was at a relative's
memorial service.

102
00:07:42,208 --> 00:07:43,375
So, what are you reading?

103
00:07:43,458 --> 00:07:45,125
Well, that one is--

104
00:07:45,208 --> 00:07:47,375
[AKANE]
Spaceship, huh?

105
00:07:47,458 --> 00:07:48,958
Yeah.

106
00:07:49,041 --> 00:07:51,333
I just happened to pick it up
completely at random, honest.

107
00:07:51,416 --> 00:07:53,250
[AKANE]
Oh, it's Red King.

108
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:54,125
Huh?

109
00:07:54,208 --> 00:07:55,333
[AKANE]
Without a doubt,

110
00:07:55,416 --> 00:07:57,375
his third model is best
out of all of them.

111
00:07:57,458 --> 00:08:00,708
Whoa. Wait, Shinjo.
You're into kaiju?

112
00:08:00,791 --> 00:08:02,666
[AKANE]
Hm?  I sure am.

113
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:05,583
There's no way!
Here, lemme see that.

114
00:08:07,375 --> 00:08:09,291
Tell me what this one is called.

115
00:08:09,375 --> 00:08:11,208
What? Are you talking
about Yadokarin?

116
00:08:11,291 --> 00:08:13,916
[gasps]
Then what about over here?

117
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:18,500
Oh, it'll come to me...
Female Majaba!

118
00:08:18,583 --> 00:08:19,958
That's Chaos Jirak.

119
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:21,875
Abnu Ogma, I think?

120
00:08:21,958 --> 00:08:27,500
Of course I know this one!
It's Gomora! With uh...

121
00:08:27,583 --> 00:08:29,125
Reionic Burst!

122
00:08:29,208 --> 00:08:31,291
You're amazing!

123
00:08:31,375 --> 00:08:32,375
[AKANE]
Hm?

124
00:08:32,458 --> 00:08:34,750
[UTSUMI] No, I mean...
Check it out!

125
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:37,916
I wish I had bought this
when they were available.

126
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,958
[AKANE]
Ultra Mech Selection mark two?

127
00:08:40,041 --> 00:08:42,416
I saw it at Nakano
the other day.

128
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:44,375
Are you serious?

129
00:08:44,458 --> 00:08:44,916
[AKANE]
Mm-hm!

130
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:45,791
[UTSUMI gasps]

131
00:08:45,875 --> 00:08:48,208
Hey! Let's go there together!

132
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:53,166
[UTSUMI gasps]
...Meaning you and me?

133
00:08:58,083 --> 00:08:59,958
[RIKKA]
Hello, please excuse me.

134
00:09:00,041 --> 00:09:03,708
My parents aren't around,
so don't worry about it.

135
00:09:03,791 --> 00:09:04,833
They're not here?

136
00:09:04,916 --> 00:09:07,083
No, they're never
around, actually.

137
00:09:07,166 --> 00:09:08,958
They aren't? I'm sorry.

138
00:09:09,041 --> 00:09:11,625
Didn't I just tell
you not to worry?

139
00:09:11,708 --> 00:09:14,791
Besides, I have someone
who takes care of me.

140
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:18,208
I wonder if they're home.
Are you here, Alexis?

141
00:09:18,291 --> 00:09:19,833
A foreigner?

142
00:09:19,916 --> 00:09:22,416
[ALEXIS] Did you call
for me, Miss Akane?

143
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:24,333
[RIKKA gasps]
What the...?

144
00:09:24,416 --> 00:09:26,708
May I introduce you
to Alexis Kerib.

145
00:09:26,791 --> 00:09:28,208
[ALEXIS]
Salutations.

146
00:09:28,291 --> 00:09:30,000
Is he an alien?

147
00:09:30,083 --> 00:09:31,750
And where's all that
smoke coming from?

148
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:32,791
[ALEXIS]
Hm?

149
00:09:32,875 --> 00:09:35,125
[AKANE giggles]
It's cosplay, Rikka!

150
00:09:35,208 --> 00:09:36,875
He really went all out.

151
00:09:36,958 --> 00:09:39,500
[AKANE] If that smoke was real,
he'd have a big problem!

152
00:09:39,583 --> 00:09:41,458
Yeah. You kinda
got a point there.

153
00:09:41,541 --> 00:09:43,458
[ALEXIS] I apologize
for surprising you.

154
00:09:43,541 --> 00:09:45,958
It's cool. I don't know
what I was thinking.

155
00:09:46,041 --> 00:09:47,208
Sorry about that.

156
00:09:47,291 --> 00:09:50,666
[AKANE chuckles]
Rikka, you're the absolute best!

157
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:52,541
Always a hundred percent honest.

158
00:09:52,625 --> 00:09:53,916
[RIKKA]
Huh?

159
00:09:56,916 --> 00:09:59,916
[UTSUMI cheers] At long last,
it's finally mine! All mine!

160
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,500
This is a dream come true!

161
00:10:01,583 --> 00:10:02,875
[AKANE]
Glad we came?

162
00:10:02,958 --> 00:10:05,500
Yeah! I owe you
big time, Shinjo!

163
00:10:05,583 --> 00:10:08,500
This is the only decent
Space Mammy in existence!

164
00:10:08,583 --> 00:10:12,166
Hey. Do you happen to know how
long this series was out for?

165
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:15,541
Um, I'm not sure. But I'm
pretty certain there were some

166
00:10:15,625 --> 00:10:18,000
released from Super GUTS.

167
00:10:18,083 --> 00:10:20,125
[MALE ANNOUNCER A]
Classic Leader. Classic Leader,

168
00:10:20,208 --> 00:10:22,583
to the third floor
trade counter, please.

169
00:10:22,666 --> 00:10:23,791
[UTSUMI gasps]

170
00:10:23,875 --> 00:10:26,166
It looks like they
made four sets total.

171
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:27,583
Yeah...

172
00:10:27,666 --> 00:10:29,875
Whatta shame the Hexa Wing
wasn't a part of it, huh?

173
00:10:32,125 --> 00:10:37,083
♪

174
00:10:47,416 --> 00:10:50,166
[AKANE] That's exactly how
things should have been.

175
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:51,875
Because they,
like everybody else,

176
00:10:51,958 --> 00:10:53,458
were made so they would like me.

177
00:10:53,541 --> 00:10:56,583
[ALEXIS] I'm glad to
see it's going so well.

178
00:10:56,666 --> 00:10:58,166
[AKANE]
You really think so?

179
00:10:58,250 --> 00:11:00,500
[ALEXIS]
Of course. I'm impressed.

180
00:11:00,583 --> 00:11:04,083
The only person who can
create such a magnificent kaiju,

181
00:11:04,166 --> 00:11:06,458
is you.

182
00:11:06,541 --> 00:11:08,125
What's with this?

183
00:11:08,208 --> 00:11:10,875
How come Gridman
isn't appearing?

184
00:11:15,666 --> 00:11:21,375
[BORR]
Utsumi! Hey! Wake up!

185
00:11:21,458 --> 00:11:26,583
What the heck? It's useless.
Nothing can wake them up.

186
00:11:26,666 --> 00:11:29,583
Th-That kaiju has
to be the reason.

187
00:11:29,666 --> 00:11:31,000
Nothing can touch it.

188
00:11:31,083 --> 00:11:34,125
However, it's not
causing damage, either.

189
00:11:34,208 --> 00:11:37,916
Only those three
are fast asleep.

190
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,875
Think they're having
a good dream?

191
00:11:40,958 --> 00:11:42,083
[MAX]
A dream.

192
00:11:43,875 --> 00:11:48,833
[inaudible]

193
00:11:49,958 --> 00:11:51,458
[YUTA gasps]

194
00:12:00,083 --> 00:12:02,166
[AKANE]
What're you doing?

195
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:03,916
Let's hurry up!

196
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,250
Right.

197
00:12:10,708 --> 00:12:12,583
Wh-What do you want?

198
00:12:12,666 --> 00:12:15,541
Oh, don't you even think about
coming in here all soaking wet!

199
00:12:15,625 --> 00:12:17,666
Invest in a damn umbrella!

200
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:19,291
[ANTI]
Bring out Gridman!

201
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:22,125
Crushing him is the only
thing that matters to me!

202
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:24,750
Unfortunately, Gridman's out
on vacation today.

203
00:12:24,833 --> 00:12:26,333
Don't screw with me!

204
00:12:26,416 --> 00:12:29,916
It's the truth. As long as that
kaiju out there is undefeated,

205
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:33,208
Gridman won't appear.

206
00:12:33,291 --> 00:12:34,833
[ANTI]
All right then.

207
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:39,625
[ANTI grunts]

208
00:12:39,708 --> 00:12:41,291
[ANTI shouts]

209
00:12:43,083 --> 00:12:44,208
[ANTI shouts]

210
00:12:44,291 --> 00:12:46,541
That guy's got a one
track mind, doesn't he?

211
00:12:46,625 --> 00:12:48,458
[ANTI yells]

212
00:12:48,541 --> 00:12:50,458
[AKANE]
Huh? What's that about?

213
00:12:50,541 --> 00:12:51,958
[ALEXIS]
Strange.

214
00:12:52,041 --> 00:12:55,333
I wonder if Anti changed his
mind and likes Gridman now.

215
00:12:55,416 --> 00:12:57,500
[AKANE] That's not what
I was talking about.

216
00:12:57,583 --> 00:12:59,125
Didn't you deal with him?

217
00:12:59,208 --> 00:13:02,083
[ALEXIS] Uh, sorry.
He got away from me.

218
00:13:02,166 --> 00:13:03,833
But wouldn't it be
nice if Gridman

219
00:13:03,916 --> 00:13:06,791
were to disappear
for good?

220
00:13:08,916 --> 00:13:10,083
Yeah.

221
00:13:18,250 --> 00:13:21,375
[YUTA]
Akane... Akane...

222
00:13:21,458 --> 00:13:22,666
[YUTA]
Akane?

223
00:13:25,750 --> 00:13:27,541
[AKANE gasps]

224
00:13:27,625 --> 00:13:30,416
Everything okay?

225
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:33,958
[AKANE] Oh, yeah.
Just spaced out for a second.

226
00:13:34,041 --> 00:13:36,958
I like walking around in
cemeteries during the summer.

227
00:13:37,041 --> 00:13:40,416
During the summer?
But it's October.

228
00:13:43,666 --> 00:13:44,708
It feels like...

229
00:13:44,791 --> 00:13:46,000
[AKANE]
Huh?

230
00:13:46,083 --> 00:13:49,708
[YUTA] It feels like
I'm forgetting something.

231
00:13:49,791 --> 00:13:53,125
[AKANE] Of course you are.
You've got amnesia.

232
00:13:53,208 --> 00:13:57,333
[YUTA] True, but...
something's lacking.

233
00:13:57,416 --> 00:13:58,875
[AKANE]
What is?

234
00:13:58,958 --> 00:14:00,291
[YUTA]
It's hard to explain, but...

235
00:14:00,375 --> 00:14:02,375
[AKANE]
Who cares about any of that?

236
00:14:02,458 --> 00:14:04,750
[AKANE] If you're having fun,
then what does it matter?

237
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:06,416
[YUTA]
That's not what I mean.

238
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:09,375
I feel like there's
something I've gotta do.

239
00:14:12,791 --> 00:14:15,125
And it's something even
more important than me?

240
00:14:15,208 --> 00:14:18,916
No! It's important, even to you.

241
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:24,125
Something only I can do.
Something that I must do.

242
00:14:24,208 --> 00:14:26,250
[gasps]

243
00:14:41,375 --> 00:14:42,458
[AKANE]
Don't!

244
00:14:45,916 --> 00:14:47,041
[UTSUMI]
Hot damn!

245
00:14:47,125 --> 00:14:50,416
I've never bought so
much in my whole life!

246
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:52,416
Hold on. That's all
you're getting?

247
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:55,250
[AKANE] Yeah, I didn't really
see anything I wanted, so...

248
00:14:55,333 --> 00:14:57,625
[UTSUMI]
Your loss. You know what?

249
00:14:57,708 --> 00:15:00,208
I always wanted a friend
like you to hang out with!

250
00:15:00,291 --> 00:15:02,083
You're so cool!

251
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:05,291
[AKANE]
Hey, you wanna come over?

252
00:15:05,375 --> 00:15:06,833
[UTSUMI]
Huh?

253
00:15:06,916 --> 00:15:09,000
[AKANE] Didn't you say that you
wanted to watch Ultra Force?

254
00:15:09,083 --> 00:15:12,708
I've got Ultra Coliseum,
Nice, and Technicolor Q.

255
00:15:12,791 --> 00:15:14,000
[UTSUMI]
But...

256
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:21,041
Don't worry. It'll be okay.
My folks aren't around.

257
00:15:21,125 --> 00:15:23,208
You could even
stay if you want.

258
00:15:24,750 --> 00:15:26,000
[UTSUMI]
This is wrong.

259
00:15:26,083 --> 00:15:26,916
[AKANE]
Huh?

260
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,750
This would never
actually happen.

261
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:33,083
So many good things, one right
after another. But still...

262
00:15:33,166 --> 00:15:34,500
Why now?

263
00:15:35,625 --> 00:15:37,541
[TATSUMI]
It's finally summer break!

264
00:15:37,625 --> 00:15:39,458
[HAYAKAWA] Those finals
really killed me, though.

265
00:15:39,541 --> 00:15:42,666
[MARUSAN] Hey, Akane, let's all
go somewhere in the time off!

266
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:45,208
Yeah, that would be awesome!
My vote's for Sea.

267
00:15:45,291 --> 00:15:46,583
[MARUSAN]
Sea again, really?

268
00:15:46,666 --> 00:15:47,750
[FURUMA]
Yeah, Sea!

269
00:15:47,833 --> 00:15:48,583
[TATSUMI]
I've got an annual pass!

270
00:15:48,666 --> 00:15:51,958
Hey, Rikka, you coming, too?

271
00:15:52,041 --> 00:15:53,208
I think I'll pass.

272
00:15:53,291 --> 00:15:56,208
Aw, really? Why?

273
00:15:56,291 --> 00:15:58,458
You have plenty of
friends to go with you.

274
00:15:58,541 --> 00:16:01,083
Sure, but you're also
one of my friends.

275
00:16:01,166 --> 00:16:05,500
Yeah, I know that. But still...

276
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:17,416
[AKANE gasps]

277
00:16:26,916 --> 00:16:30,875
This is all a dream.
Here's your watch back.

278
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:36,541
Wouldn't it be better if you
could dream forever, though?

279
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:39,083
Dreams are things
you wake up from.

280
00:16:39,166 --> 00:16:43,333
Everyone does.
Even you, Shinjo.

281
00:16:45,375 --> 00:16:49,583
But if I could, I would stay
inside a dream forever.

282
00:16:49,666 --> 00:16:54,166
[YUTA] I can't join you.
Gridman is calling me.

283
00:17:06,916 --> 00:17:10,791
[UTSUMI] This is all a dream.
None of my friends are here.

284
00:17:10,875 --> 00:17:12,416
[AKANE]
What about me?

285
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:14,500
Am I not your friend?

286
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:19,583
If this was how we
had actually met,

287
00:17:19,666 --> 00:17:23,208
and like, if we had done this
stuff in real life some time,

288
00:17:23,291 --> 00:17:25,708
then I think we could
have been friends.

289
00:17:36,125 --> 00:17:39,750
[RIKKA]
This is a dream, right?

290
00:17:39,833 --> 00:17:41,791
[AKANE]
What's wrong with a dream?

291
00:17:41,875 --> 00:17:45,708
Let's keep it going,
just like this.

292
00:17:45,791 --> 00:17:47,583
I'm sorry, but I can't.

293
00:17:47,666 --> 00:17:51,125
But you have to!
I told you before!

294
00:17:51,208 --> 00:17:54,666
You were born already
as my friend, Rikka.

295
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:58,500
And not just you,
but everybody else, too.

296
00:18:00,791 --> 00:18:02,458
[RIKKA]
I'm sorry.

297
00:18:02,541 --> 00:18:04,583
[MALE ANNOUNCER B]
Stopping next.

298
00:18:15,041 --> 00:18:17,666
[AKANE] Even in dreams
I can't reach them?

299
00:18:22,958 --> 00:18:24,791
[YUTA]
Utsumi! Rikka!

300
00:18:24,875 --> 00:18:26,833
[UTSUMI]
Yuta! It's Yuta!

301
00:18:26,916 --> 00:18:30,708
[RIKKA] Hibiki!
I remembered everything, too!

302
00:18:30,791 --> 00:18:34,125
[YUTA] We have something.
Something only we can do!

303
00:18:34,208 --> 00:18:39,041
Something we must do!
Right? Gridman?

304
00:18:41,416 --> 00:18:45,375
[GRIDMAN] Right! I had faith,
and waited for you!

305
00:18:45,458 --> 00:18:49,333
[GRIDMAN shouts]

306
00:18:57,250 --> 00:19:00,791
[KAIJU roars]

307
00:19:00,875 --> 00:19:02,208
What the...?

308
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:07,041
The kaiju materialized.

309
00:19:07,125 --> 00:19:09,166
G-Grid kinesis?

310
00:19:09,250 --> 00:19:11,916
Looks like Gridman only
woke up on the other side.

311
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:15,291
Meaning we've gotta deal
with this kaiju ourselves.

312
00:19:15,375 --> 00:19:18,708
All right! Then let's shrink
down our output and go as four!

313
00:19:18,791 --> 00:19:22,375
[ALL]
Access code...

314
00:19:33,083 --> 00:19:34,333
[ANTI gasps]

315
00:19:59,458 --> 00:20:04,208
[ALL] War God Combine!
Powered Zenon!

316
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:13,666
[ALL shouts]
Powered Breaker!

317
00:20:17,875 --> 00:20:24,375
[ALL]
Powered Axe! Jumbo Saber. Slash!

318
00:20:38,416 --> 00:20:41,583
[phone rings]

319
00:20:41,666 --> 00:20:43,125
[CALIBUR]
What do you want?

320
00:20:43,208 --> 00:20:47,583
[ANTI] The kaiju is gone now.
Why hasn't Gridman appeared?

321
00:20:47,666 --> 00:20:49,958
[CALIBUR]
Because there's no need to.

322
00:20:50,041 --> 00:20:53,083
G-Gridman will not be
facing you in battle.

323
00:20:53,166 --> 00:20:54,333
[ANTI]
Why not?

324
00:20:54,416 --> 00:20:55,833
[CALIBUR]
Because you're a living being

325
00:20:55,916 --> 00:20:57,791
who possesses a heart.

326
00:20:57,875 --> 00:21:01,583
[ANTI]
You're wrong. I am a kaiju!

327
00:21:10,083 --> 00:21:13,208
What should I do now?

328
00:21:13,291 --> 00:21:14,833
What should I...

329
00:21:35,708 --> 00:21:38,375
[YUTA grunts]

330
00:21:42,041 --> 00:21:45,166
[BORR cuckles]
Morning, sleepyheads.

331
00:21:45,250 --> 00:21:48,750
Hey... Where's Gridman?!

332
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:52,041
[GRIDMAN]
Yuta, I'm right here.

333
00:21:52,125 --> 00:21:54,166
Thanks so much, Gridman.

334
00:21:54,250 --> 00:21:57,125
Because of you, we were able
to come back from the dream.

335
00:21:57,208 --> 00:21:58,416
[GRIDMAN]
But there's another.

336
00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:02,208
Another human who must
wake from their dream.

337
00:22:02,291 --> 00:22:03,833
You mean Shinjo.

338
00:22:11,083 --> 00:22:15,583
[RIKKA] Hey. There's something
I think all of you need to hear.

339
00:22:17,041 --> 00:22:22,000
♪


